Raw dev notes -- NotebookLM: From Cookie Hell to Smoke Tests (early-mid March 2026)

The early days of the NotebookLM wrapper were rough. I was extracting cookies via Playwright,
validating them, backing them up -- and it STILL broke constantly. This week was about
stabilizing the foundation.

Key work:
- Built a comprehensive 16-endpoint smoke test script
- Native auth via storage_state.json replaced manual cookie extraction
- Added crash-resilient session refresh
- Heartbeat system with JSONL logging and status.json
- Keep-alive supervisor loop as safety net
- Fixed UTF-8 encoding issues on Windows for heartbeat output
- Port moved to 8001 to avoid conflicts

The big "aha": I was overcomplicating auth. Playwright's persistent browser profile stores
cookies internally. No need to extract, validate, or back them up. Just reuse the same
browser profile directory. All the cookie management code became dead weight.

Struggles:
- storage_state.json kept getting overwritten with invalid cookies on auth failures
- Repeated failures needed exponential backoff
- Windows-specific encoding issues with heartbeat output

This was the "make it work reliably" phase before the browser-as-runtime rewrite.
